In the lectures, the basic principles of computer architecture and design will be given. The student learn also how to choose the best in price-quality scale components for a computer and how to assamble a computer using those components.
All assessments and distribution of additional learning material will be in Moodle learning environment.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course gives to the student the primary knowledge about computer hardware and it is a prerequisite for other special courses about  computer hardware.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students are expected: Knows the basic units of a personal computer (PC); Is capable to find information in the internet and assess the information relaiability; Knows how to assamble the PC; Is capable to select optimal components and accessuars (price-quality scale) for a computer. Knows the general outline of computer mashine code; Is capable to draw the simplest logial diagrams of computer components; Understands the principles of direct memory access (DMA) and interupt request (IRQ); Makes difference between the synchronous and asynchronous data transmission; Knows, how cache- and virtual memory works; Knows, how the central processing unit (CPU) works; Knows, how the pipeline works.
